- var pagetype = "styleguide"
- var page = "Color"

doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    include ./layout/_head.jade
  body(class='#{pagetype}')
    header.styleguide-header
      include ./layout/_navbar.jade
      
    main.styleguide-container(role='main')

      .container
          
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h2 Color palette
            p You can use your own brand colors for your version of this application. We have defined a few color names based on the material design guidelines.
        
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h3.text-primary Primary color      
          .col-md-6
            p When using a primary color in your palette, this color should be the most widely used across all screens and components.
          .col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-primary.center Our default primary color is #29abe2.
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h3.text-secondary Secondary color     
          .col-md-6
            p Palettes with a secondary color may use this color to indicate a related action or information.
            p The secondary color may be a darker or lighter variation of the primary color.
          .col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-secondary.center  Our default secondary color is #1f80aa.
        
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h3.text-accent Accent color 
          .col-md-6
            p The accent should be used for the floating action button and interactive elements, such as:
            ul
              li Text fields and cursors
              li Text selection
              li Progress bars
              li Selection controls, buttons, and sliders
              li Links
                            
          .col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-accent.center  Our default accent color is #ffc142.
          
      
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h3 State color
            p For states in forms, messages and other feedback we use state colors to indicate whether user actions were performed succesfully or failed for example.
        .row
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-success.center Success color
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-error.center Error color
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-warning.center Warning color
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-info.center Info color
      
        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h2.header Usage 
            br
            h4 Background color
            p To apply a background color, just add the color name as a class to the element.
        .row
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-primary.center This is a card with a style-primary class
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-primary-dark.center This is a card with a style-primary-dark class
        .row      
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-default.center This is a card with a style-default class
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body.style-default-bright.center This is a card with a style-default-light class

        .row
          .col-xs-12
            h4 Text color
            p To apply a text color, just apply text-{color} to the text element.
        .row
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body
                p.text-primary.center This is a paragraph with a text-primary class
          .col-xs-12.col-md-6
            .card
              .card-body
                p.text-primary-dark.center This is a paragraph with a text-primary-dark class
          
        .row
          .col.s12.l8
            h2.header Customize
            p Material has a few basic theme colors. These colors can be changed in the css/ src/theme folder. Simply duplicate the example-theme.scss file and change it to your designed theme name. Then include the new file as import in the base materialize.scss file. 
  
    include ./layout/_scripts.jade
